# CONTEXT.md — make the loop yours

Copy this file to `CONTEXT.md` (same folder as SKILL.md) and fill it in.
The reflect loop loads it before every run.

## Who I am
<!-- One paragraph: role, company/stage, what a "big" decision means for you in $ or impact. -->
Example: Solo founder of a B2B SaaS at ~$10k MRR. A $5k mistake is survivable;
a positioning flip-flop is not.

## Settled decisions — NEVER re-litigate these
<!-- Decisions you've made deliberately and don't want re-opened by every analysis.
     The loop may flag genuinely new evidence against them, but never quietly reopens. -->
- Example: We are bootstrapped; fundraising is off the table until $50k MRR.
- Example: Pricing is flat-rate; no usage-based pricing.

## My recurring decision types
<!-- What you'll actually reflect on — helps the loop pick lenses fast. -->
- Example: feature build-vs-kill, channel investments, hiring first roles, partnership offers.

## Risk posture
<!-- How you want recommendations calibrated. -->
Example: Aggressive on reversible bets, conservative on anything touching
customer trust or public commitments.

## Review cadence
<!-- When the loop should set review-by dates. -->
Example: tactical calls 3 weeks out, strategic calls one quarter out.

## My brain files (optional)
<!-- Paths to your personal knowledge files — notes, a CLAUDE.md, a lessons
     journal, a strategy doc. The loop skims these while framing a decision,
     because your own recorded experience outranks any generic mental model. -->
- Example: ~/notes/BRAIN.md
- Example: ./CLAUDE.md
- Example: ./docs/strategy/positioning.md
